    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="5">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and the two bearing retainer rings from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302431">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302431" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302431" filename="../figg13/g1302431.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Remove Bolts and Bearing Retainer Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the coupling snap ring from the groove in the mainshaft (located in the bore of the
                auxiliary drive gear) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302432">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302432" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302432" filename="../figg13/g1302432.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 32. Remove Coupling Snap Ring From Mainshaft Groove</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap against the front of the mainshaft to move the auxiliary drive gear bearing to the rear,
                exposing the bearing snap ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to remove the auxiliary drive gear assembly from the case bore and from the
                splines of the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302433">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302433" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302433" filename="../figg13/g1302433.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 33. Use Pry Bars to Remove Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the groove in the auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302434">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302434" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302434" filename="../figg13/g1302434.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 34. Remove Snap Ring From Groove in Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press or use the driver to remove the bearing from the auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302435">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302435" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302435" filename="../figg13/g1302435.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Press or Use Drive to Remove Bearing From Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
